one, upon very simple modeling

00:29:16.470 --> 00:29:21.210
of and the analysis of how
quickly Chinese growth is

00:29:21.210 --> 00:29:24.510
and what point they will
reach a level relative to ours

00:29:24.510 --> 00:29:26.300
if they keep growing very rapidly,

00:29:26.300 --> 00:29:28.470
and India, and then it is based upon

00:29:28.470 --> 00:29:33.130
how long it took Japan and
Korea to get up to the level.

00:29:33.130 --> 00:29:35.600
Korea was the poorest country in the world

00:29:35.600 --> 00:29:38.300
after the Korean War,
they had no resources

00:29:38.300 --> 00:29:40.483
and they just hard work and,

00:29:42.260 --> 00:29:44.860
and education, really, is what made Korea,

00:29:44.860 --> 00:29:47.239
and some US help, but
Korea did a lot of things

00:29:47.239 --> 00:29:51.890
on their own, and so the
best you could hope for

00:29:51.890 --> 00:29:53.840
in a country that started very poor

00:29:53.840 --> 00:29:56.420
is in 40, 50 years they can
get up to the first rank

00:29:56.420 --> 00:29:59.613
of places, so this is the
challenge to democracy.

